org.graphstream.algorithm.measure
Class GraphNervousness

java.lang.Object
  org.graphstream.algorithm.measure.GraphNervousness
All Implemented Interfaces:
Algorithm, org.graphstream.stream.ElementSink
public class GraphNervousness
extends java.lang.Object
implements Algorithm, org.graphstream.stream.ElementSink

The graph nervousness is a measure that give for each step of a dynamic graph a ratio between the number of structural events ( addition and removal of nodes and edges) and the number of elements (nodes and edges) in the graph. This measure is different from the Element Nervousness even different from the average element nervousness.
